						               													<description>EL ALAMEIN: Battles in North Africa, 1942, is an operational simulation, based on the KURSK Game System, of the battles between Rommel&amp;rsquo;s Panzer Armee Afrika and Montgomery&amp;rsquo;s Eighth Army near El Alamein from July through October 1942. The outcome of these bitterly-fought clashes finally ended Rommel&amp;rsquo;s eastern drive towards Alexandria and the Suez Canal, and forced a defeated and burned-out Panzer Armee Afrika to begin the long retreat west towards Tunisia&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are three scenarios; The First Battle of El Alamein (July 1942), Alam Halfa (Sept 1942) and Battle of El Alamein (Oct 1942).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Time Scale: 1 day (24 hours) per game turn&amp;#10;Map Scale: 5 kilometers per hex&amp;#10;Unit Size: regiment/brigade/division&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Components:&amp;#10;One 22&amp;rsquo;&amp;rsquo; x 28&amp;rdquo; hexagonal grid Map Sheet (with Turn Record Track and Scenario OOB Set Up Locations incorporated)&amp;#10;255 &amp;frac12;&amp;rdquo; cardboard Counters&amp;#10;One 9&amp;rdquo; x 11&amp;frac12; &amp;rdquo; map-fold Rules Booklet&amp;#10;One 7&amp;frac14;&amp;rdquo; x 10&amp;rdquo; combined Combat Results Table and Terrain Effects Chart&amp;#10;One 7&amp;frac14;&amp;rdquo; x 12&amp;rdquo; Scenario Variation Chart&amp;#10;Two 8&amp;frac12;&amp;rdquo; x 11&amp;rdquo; Errata Sheets (as 31 July 1973)&amp;#10;One small six-sided Die&amp;#10;One SPI 12&amp;rdquo; x 15&amp;rdquo; x 1&amp;rdquo; flat 24 compartment plastic Game Box (with clear compartment tray covers) and clear plastic game cover with Title Sheet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
